-- 
South Africa to Intervene on Kansai, Freeworld Deal, Business Day Reports

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-08-23T05:13:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-23/south-africa-to-intervene-on-kansai-freeworld-deal-business-day-reports.html
South Africa ’s Department of Trade
and Industry plans to intervene in Kansai Paint Co.’s takeover
of  Freeworld Coatings Ltd. (FWD)  on grounds of public interest,
Business Day reported, citing Kansai’s legal adviser, Jean
Meijer.  The department’s application will be heard at the end of
August, the Johannesburg-based newspaper reported. The country’s
Competition Tribunal suspended a condition that required Kansai
to divest of Freeworld’s automotive coatings joint venture in
Port Elizabeth and Durban with DuPont & Co., Business Day said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  